  "body": "<!--\r\nNeed help?\r\nRefer to our contributing guidelines for additional information about making a good issue:\r\nhttps://github.com/ethereum-optimism/.github/blob/master/CONTRIBUTING.md\r\n-->\r\n\r\n**Is your feature request related to a problem? Please describe.**\r\nRunning /ops (`sudo docker-compose up`) generates enough logging to exhaust disk space (about 5GB/day in my case), leading to host issues.\r\n\r\n**Describe the solution you'd like**\r\nWarn users about this and point them to mitigations. In my case I configured `/etc/docker/daemon.json` like this:\r\n\r\n```json\r\n{\r\n  \"log-driver\": \"json-file\",\r\n  \"log-opts\": {\r\n    \"max-size\": \"100m\",\r\n    \"max-file\": \"3\"\r\n  }\r\n}\r\n```\r\n\r\n(After learning about disk exhaustion the hard way.)\r\n\r\n**Describe alternatives you've considered**\r\nIt might be possible to configure something similar by default in `docker-compose.yml`.\r\n\r\n**Additional context**\r\nhttps://docs.docker.com/config/containers/logging/configure/\r\n",
