    "body": "Thanks for pointing this out. The `docker-compose` setup isn't meant to be ran in production, it exists for local development and integration testing purposes. Open to having a PR opened that updates `ops/README` with this information\r\n\r\nYou should be able to increase the configured polling intervals which would decrease the amount of logs being generated.\r\n- https://github.com/ethereum-optimism/optimism/blob/87459d5e4dcc843fc0758c4b1acf7bf957265ee8/ops/envs/dtl.env#L7\r\n- https://github.com/ethereum-optimism/optimism/blob/87459d5e4dcc843fc0758c4b1acf7bf957265ee8/ops/envs/geth.env#L8\r\n\r\nAlso you should consider adding your user to the `docker` group so that you don't need to use `sudo` when running `docker` commands, see https://docs.docker.com/engine/install/linux-postinstall/",
